originalText.text: When seeking out a wedding photographer, we wanted someone who knew how to capture moments without awkward and lengthy staging.  Amy's documentary-style photography delivered more than we ever imagined possible!  Her calm and relaxed energy made everyone feel comfortable and easy, and our wedding photos reflect the joy and soaring spirit of the day.  Amy's work even inspired us to get our daughter a camera for Christmas and, of course, lessons with Amy!

originalText.text: Amy Milstein needs to be the photographer you choose for any occasion, especially your wedding. I searched through so many photographers and everything looked the same. Until I found Amy. Amy's photographs capture a moment in motion. They are candid, and authentic and transport you back in time to that exact second and you can feel and hear and see and smell everything around you. There is just no other way to describe it - it's pure magic what she does. We only wanted a handful of 'posed' photos at the Church with our immediate family and Amy made those beautiful, and still captured the candid moments in those which we wound up loving more than the ones when we are just standing and smiling at the camera. We also could not tell that Amy was there - it's like she got access to Harry's invisibility cloak or something. We wanted to have a video of our wedding also and Amy gave us an incredible recommendation. Her photos presented are both in color and black and white, and I do recommend having her select which ones should be which! She's got such a great eye and taste for it. I could gush on and on forever about her - but it's safe to say our wedding would not have been captured as beautifully and honestly if it wasn't for Amy. We cannot wait to use her again for all of our future celebrations in life!

originalText.text: Amy met all our expectations and then some for our wedding photos. Amy's style of photography is captivating. Wedding photos can be so sterile and boring, but not with Amy. Not only is she incredibly talented, but she's a real joy to work with. She is friendly, easy going and a great communicator. I'd highly recommend Amy and hope to work with her again some day!

originalText.text: Amy photographed my fiance and I for our engagement photos in Dumbo Brooklyn. I found her special on Groupon and reached out. Her response time was rapid and she was extremely flexible when scheduling which is hard with a first responder job. Amy spent so much time with us, didn't rush and made sure she had perfect shots. She is very personable and easy to work with taking the time to find out what you envision. Ordering was a breeze and her prices are amazing for the quality of work she provides. She marked the occasion for us perfectly and I look forward to hiring her to capture all those important moments on our wedding day.
